level=INFO msg=text content="Done. Read-only exploration, no changes made.\n\n## Top-level files\n\nThe repo root contains config and tooling files plus these key directories:\n\n- **Dirs**: `cmd/`, `internal/`, `webui/`, `proto/`, `proposals/`, `examples/`, `containers/`, `n8n-node/`, `prebuilt/`, `images/`\n- **Go**: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `generate.go`\n- **Build/tooling**: `mise.toml`, `buf.gen.yaml`, `buf.yaml`, `sqlc.yaml`, `.dbmate.toml`, `Dockerfile`(+`.dev`)\n- **Compose**: `docker-compose.yml`, `.dev.yml`, `.test.yml`\n- **Deploy/CI**: `fly.toml`, `.github/`, `.conform.yaml`, `.release-please-config.json`, `renovate.json`\n- **Docs/secrets**: `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `sops.env.yml`, `github-app-manifest.json`\n- A built `xagent` binary (~47MB) and `claude-session.jsonl` are also present.\n\n## README.md\n\nXAGENT runs coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, GitHub Copilot) inside remote Docker sandboxes. Highlights: self-hosted runners, GitHub/Jira event integrations, and an MCP server for task management. Covers quick start (install via `mise`, API key config, `workspaces.yaml`, `xagent runner`), workspace examples, debugging (`xagent logs`/`shell`/`containers`, `verbose: true`), local dev, and an events/links subscription model.\n\n## go.mod\n\n- **Module**: `github.com/icholy/xagent`, **Go 1.26.0**\n- **Direct deps** of note: `connectrpc.com/connect` (Connect RPC), `jackc/pgx/v5` (Postgres), `modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk` (MCP), `docker/docker` + `docker/cli`, `urfave/cli/v3`, `google/go-github/v88`, `zitadel/oidc` + `zitadel-go` (auth), OpenTelemetry stack, `yaml.v3`, `gotest.tools/v3`.\n- **Tools**: buf, moq, sqlc, stringer.\n\n## `func main` locations\n\nThree entry points:\n- `cmd/xagent/main.go:12` — the main CLI\n- `cmd/migrate/main.go:10` — DB migrations\n- `cmd/dummymcp/main.go:14` — a dummy MCP server\n\n(The fourth match was just text inside `claude-session.jsonl`, not real code.)\n\n## `go vet ./...`\n\nPassed cleanly — no output, no warnings or errors."
